#. HTML: <section class="sutta" id="sn3.11"><article><div class="hgroup"><p class="division">
msgctxt "sn3.11:0.1"
msgid "Saṃyutta Nikāya 3 "
msgstr "Linked Discourses 3 "

#. HTML: </p><p>
#. VAR: 2. Dutiyavagga → aputtakavaggo (bj)
msgctxt "sn3.11:0.2"
msgid "2. Dutiyavagga "
msgstr "2. Childless "

#. HTML: </p><h1>
msgctxt "sn3.11:0.3"
msgid "11. Sattajaṭilasutta "
msgstr "11. Seven Matted-Hair Ascetics "

#. HTML: </h1></div><p>
#. REF: sc1
msgctxt "sn3.11:1.1"
msgid "Ekaṃ samayaṃ bhagavā sāvatthiyaṃ viharati pubbārāme migāramātupāsāde. "
msgstr "At one time the Buddha was staying near Sāvatthī in the Eastern Monastery, the stilt longhouse of Migāra’s mother. "

#. HTML: </p><p>
msgctxt "sn3.11:1.2"
msgid "Tena kho pana samayena bhagavā sāyanhasamayaṃ paṭisallānā vuṭṭhito bahidvārakoṭṭhake nisinno hoti. "
msgstr "Then in the late afternoon, the Buddha came out of retreat and sat outside the gate. "

msgctxt "sn3.11:1.3"
msgid "Atha kho rājā pasenadi kosalo yena bhagavā tenupasaṅkami; upasaṅkamitvā bhagavantaṃ abhivādetvā ekamantaṃ nisīdi. "
msgstr "Then King Pasenadi of Kosala went up to the Buddha, bowed, and sat down to one side. "

# NOTE: See PTS dict under khari for vividha=vivadha=kāja.
#. HTML: </p><p>
#. REF: pts1ed1.78, pts2ed1.177, sc2
msgctxt "sn3.11:2.1"
msgid "Tena kho pana samayena satta ca jaṭilā satta ca nigaṇṭhā satta ca acelakā satta ca ekasāṭakā satta ca paribbājakā parūḷhakacchanakhalomā khārivividhamādāya bhagavato avidūre atikkamanti. "
msgstr "Now at that time seven matted-hair ascetics, seven Jain ascetics, seven naked ascetics, seven one-cloth ascetics, and seven wanderers passed by not far from the Buddha. Their armpits and bodies were hairy, and their nails were long; and they carried their stuff with shoulder-poles. "

#. HTML: </p><p>
msgctxt "sn3.11:2.2"
msgid "Atha kho rājā pasenadi kosalo uṭṭhāyāsanā ekaṃsaṃ uttarāsaṅgaṃ karitvā dakkhiṇajāṇumaṇḍalaṃ pathaviyaṃ nihantvā yena te satta ca jaṭilā satta ca nigaṇṭhā satta ca acelakā satta ca ekasāṭakā satta ca paribbājakā tenañjaliṃ paṇāmetvā tikkhattuṃ nāmaṃ sāvesi: "
msgstr "Then King Pasenadi got up from his seat, arranged his robe over one shoulder, knelt with his right knee on the ground, raised his joined palms toward those various ascetics, and pronounced his name three times: "

msgctxt "sn3.11:2.3"
msgid "“rājāhaṃ, bhante, pasenadi kosalo … pe … rājāhaṃ, bhante, pasenadi kosalo”ti. "
msgstr "“Sirs, I am Pasenadi, king of Kosala! … I am Pasenadi, king of Kosala!” "

#. HTML: </p><p>
#. REF: pts2ed1.178, sc3
msgctxt "sn3.11:3.1"
msgid "Atha kho rājā pasenadi kosalo acirapakkantesu tesu sattasu ca jaṭilesu sattasu ca nigaṇṭhesu sattasu ca acelakesu sattasu ca ekasāṭakesu sattasu ca paribbājakesu yena bhagavā tenupasaṅkami; upasaṅkamitvā bhagavantaṃ abhivādetvā ekamantaṃ nisīdi. Ekamantaṃ nisinno kho rājā pasenadi kosalo bhagavantaṃ etadavoca: "
msgstr "Then, soon after those ascetics had left, King Pasenadi went up to the Buddha, bowed, sat down to one side, and said to him, "

# NOTE: I follow the PTS reading of the parallel passage at Ud 6.2. Otherwise this implicates Pasenadi in making a direct lie to the Buddha. Of course this is possible, but following the principle of least meaning it is preferable to assume that here, as usual, Pasenadi is acting in good faith.
msgctxt "sn3.11:3.2"
msgid "“ye te, bhante, loke arahanto vā arahattamaggaṃ vā samāpannā ete tesaṃ aññatarā”ti. "
msgstr "“Sir, are they among those in the world who are perfected ones or who have entered the path to perfection?” "

#. HTML: </p><p>
#. REF: sc4
msgctxt "sn3.11:4.1"
msgid "“Dujjānaṃ kho etaṃ, mahārāja, tayā gihinā kāmabhoginā puttasambādhasayanaṃ ajjhāvasantena kāsikacandanaṃ paccanubhontena mālāgandhavilepanaṃ dhārayantena jātarūparajataṃ sādiyantena: ‘ime vā arahanto, ime vā arahattamaggaṃ samāpannā’ti. "
msgstr "“Great king, as a layman enjoying sensual pleasures, living at home with your children, using sandalwood imported from Kāsi, wearing garlands, perfumes, and makeup, and accepting gold and money, it’s hard for you to know who is perfected or on the path to perfection. "

#. HTML: </p><p>
#. REF: pts1ed1.79, pts2ed1.179, sc5
msgctxt "sn3.11:5.1"
msgid "Saṃvāsena kho, mahārāja, sīlaṃ veditabbaṃ. "
msgstr "You can get to know a person’s ethics by living with them. "

msgctxt "sn3.11:5.2"
msgid "Tañca kho dīghena addhunā, na ittaraṃ; "
msgstr "But only after a long time, not casually; "

msgctxt "sn3.11:5.3"
msgid "manasikarotā, no amanasikarotā; "
msgstr "only when paying attention, not when inattentive; "

msgctxt "sn3.11:5.4"
msgid "paññavatā, no duppaññena. "
msgstr "and only by the wise, not the witless. "

msgctxt "sn3.11:5.5"
msgid "Saṃvohārena kho, mahārāja, soceyyaṃ veditabbaṃ. "
msgstr "You can get to know a person’s purity by dealing with them. … "

msgctxt "sn3.11:5.6"
msgid "Tañca kho dīghena addhunā, na ittaraṃ; "
msgstr " "

msgctxt "sn3.11:5.7"
msgid "manasikarotā, no amanasikarotā; "
msgstr " "

msgctxt "sn3.11:5.8"
msgid "paññavatā, no duppaññena. "
msgstr " "

msgctxt "sn3.11:5.9"
msgid "Āpadāsu kho, mahārāja, thāmo veditabbo. "
msgstr "You can get to know a person’s resilience in times of trouble. … "

msgctxt "sn3.11:5.10"
msgid "So ca kho dīghena addhunā, na ittaraṃ; "
msgstr " "

msgctxt "sn3.11:5.11"
msgid "manasikarotā, no amanasikarotā; "
msgstr " "

msgctxt "sn3.11:5.12"
msgid "paññavatā, no duppaññena. "
msgstr " "

msgctxt "sn3.11:5.13"
msgid "Sākacchāya, kho, mahārāja, paññā veditabbā. "
msgstr "You can get to know a person’s wisdom by discussion. "

msgctxt "sn3.11:5.14"
msgid "Sā ca kho dīghena addhunā, na ittaraṃ; "
msgstr "But only after a long time, not casually; "

msgctxt "sn3.11:5.15"
msgid "manasikarotā, no amanasikarotā; "
msgstr "only when paying attention, not when inattentive; "

msgctxt "sn3.11:5.16"
msgid "paññavatā, no duppaññenā”ti. "
msgstr "and only by the wise, not the witless.” "

#. HTML: </p><p>
#. REF: pts2ed1.180, sc6
msgctxt "sn3.11:6.1"
msgid "“Acchariyaṃ, bhante, abbhutaṃ, bhante. "
msgstr "“It’s incredible, sir, it’s amazing, "

msgctxt "sn3.11:6.2"
msgid "Yāva subhāsitamidaṃ, bhante, bhagavatā: "
msgstr "how well said this was by Master Gotama. … "

msgctxt "sn3.11:6.3"
msgid "‘dujjānaṃ kho etaṃ, mahārāja, tayā gihinā kāmabhoginā puttasambādhasayanaṃ ajjhāvasantena kāsikacandanaṃ paccanubhontena mālāgandhavilepanaṃ dhārayantena jātarūparajataṃ sādiyantena: "
msgstr " "

